date=May 15, 1997|title=NBC's Storm to Work the W.N.B.A.|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/05/15/sports/nbc-s-storm-to-work-the-wnba.html|work=The New York Times|location= |access-date= }}</ref>, studio host)\n* [[Paul Sunderland]]<ref>{{cite news |last=Hoffarth|first=Tom|date=February 2, 2012|title=TOM HOFFARTH on MEDIA: Sunderland pushes forward in post-Laker career|url=https://www.dailynews.com/2012/02/02/tom-hoffarth-on-media-sunderland-pushes-forward-in-post-laker-career/|work=Los Angeles Daily News|location= |access-date= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Stickney Jr.|first=W.H.|date=June 16, 2001|title=Notebook: After slow break-in, Johnson getting the hang of pro game|url=https://www.chron.com/sports/article/Notebook-After-slow-break-in-Johnson-getting-2032044.php|work=Houston Chronicle|location= |access-date= }}</ref> (play-by-play)\n* [[Chris Wragge]]<ref>{{cite news |last=Barron|first=David|date=June 3, 2001|title=TV/Radio Notebook: No surprise as Comets draw national exposure|url=https://www.chron.com/sports/barron/article/TV-Radio-Notebook-No-surprise-as-Comets-draw-2031873.php|work=Houston Chronicle|location= |access-date= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/chris-wragge/|title=Chris Wragge|last= |first= |date=February 20, 2008|website=CBS News|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> (sideline reporter, studio host)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://www.nbcsports.com/nba}}\n* [http://static.espn.go.com/nba/playoffs2002/s/2002/0612/1394112.html ESPN.com \u2013 NBA \u2013 PLAYOFFS2002 \u2013 The day Tesh's music might die]\n* [http://www.mpvoice.com/mpvoice/flash/nba-low.mov nba-low.mov] [[QuickTime]] MOV video: voice-over Mitch Phillips on commercial spots for the ''NBA on NBC''.\n* [http://www.hedrickonline.com/games/showtime/ NBA Showtime: NBA on NBC]\n**[http://gr.bolt.com/games/sony/sports/nba_showtime_psx.htm NBA Showtime: NBA on NBC \u2013 Game Revolution Review Page]\n* [https:/